    {
      "id": 16,
      "title": "Integrate Graphiti Entity Extraction into Document Processing Pipeline",
      "description": "Modify the document processing workflow in packages/qdrant-loader/src/qdrant_loader/core/ to incorporate Graphiti-based entity extraction and graph storage alongside existing vector embedding processes, ensuring seamless integration and backward compatibility.",
      "details": "Update the core document processing pipeline to invoke the entity extraction pipeline (from Task 5) after or in parallel with vector embedding generation. Use Graphiti's extract_entities method to identify and extract custom, domain-specific entities and relationships from each document, leveraging the configuration for entity and relationship types. After extraction, resolve entities and relationships, deduplicate as needed, and store them in the Neo4j-backed knowledge graph using Graphiti's Cypher-based integration. Ensure that the pipeline supports batch processing and can handle both vector and graph operations efficiently. Maintain backward compatibility by gating new functionality behind configuration flags and ensuring all existing document processing and embedding features remain unaffected. Update documentation and provide migration notes for any API or workflow changes.",
      "testStrategy": "1. Process a representative set of documents and verify that entities and relationships are correctly extracted and stored in the Neo4j graph, matching the configured schema. 2. Confirm that vector embeddings are still generated and stored as before, with no regressions. 3. Test with the new functionality disabled to ensure legacy workflows are unaffected. 4. Validate batch processing and error handling for both embedding and entity extraction steps. 5. Review logs and outputs to confirm that entity deduplication and relationship resolution are functioning as intended. 6. Conduct integration tests to ensure the pipeline works end-to-end in Dockerized environments.",
      "status": "pending",
      "dependencies": [
        5
      ],
      "priority": "high",
      "subtasks": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "title": "Refactor Document Processing Pipeline for Modular Integration",
